description.4: Infinity Watch can take down the bad guys no sweat…but how can they fight the law? It's up to Adam to convince Zakaius that they've been framed, but he'll have to do it quick, or face the wrath of Zakaius' master Domitian!
description.9: Clea gets a much needed assist in the Dark Dimension, and “Doc” is triumphant in a battle with Strange.
description.12: Hulk and Betty try to escape the whirlwind that has held up their lives lately, but the small town they run to has problems of its own! Someone has been kidnapping children, and Hulk aims to find out who!
description.13: To treat Captain America's paralysis, Tony Stark shrinks down to microscopic size and enters his bloodstream. The mission: to plant a biochip inside Cap's body that will restore his mobility.
description.16: While in New York, Thor and Sif are attacked by War Machine! Little do they know, he is possessed by Loki! Blitziana remembers shocking details from her past...
description.17: Can Scarlet Spider go toe-to-toe with both Kaine...and the Jackal?
description.18: The fa'ade is over! Aron, the Rogue Watcher, reveals himself at last! But what has become of Uatu, the true Watcher and friend of the FF? And do the heroes have any hope of overcoming him?
description.21: Hercules faces a double threat from Hera and his father, Zeus! Why has Hera gone to such dramatic lengths to pull the wool over Hercules' eyes? And did Taylor Madison ever truly exist? The issue that's half-comic book, half-Greek tragedy!
description.25: The Force Works team finds themselves traveling down under to face a mysterious monster! But they won't be alone, as they're joined by a new hero: Dreamguard!
description.27: A stunning betrayal leads to a devastating revelation! What does this mean for the future of the Secret Defenders?
description.29: Rory Destine daydreams about the Avengers and more of our favorite Marvel heroes after her tussle with bullies at school!
description.30: Series finale! Read the events that directly led into Punisher's first appearance in the pages of AMAZING SPIDER-MAN (1963) #129! Frank Castle's origin comes full circle, as the Punisher dons the skull n' crossbones for the very first time.
description.33: Namor plus the Ebony blade equald trouble!
description.35: Luke'is racing to'the far side'of'the galaxy'to obtain a'Jedi'Holocron'rumored to be on the'planet'Ossus. The power and knowledge that ancient device holds could give him just the edge he needs to defeat'the evil Empire! But the'Emperor has heard these rumors, too, and has sent a platoon of battle-hungry'Dark Siders'to bring the Holocron back to him. Fire up the'lightsaber, Luke! It's gonna be a long night!
description.36: While transporting contraband textbooks to a galactic schoolroom, Luke runs afoul of Imperial forces! The Empire makes their cruellest counterplay yet when they take an entire school hostage! Will the youngest members of the Rebel Alliance make their stand?
description.37: The Krath are tearing through the galaxy, laying claim to any inhabitable planets they come across, and they're crushing anyone who stands in their way! But Ulic Qel-Droma isn't just anyone; he's a Jedi, perhaps the greatest of his time. Ulic poses as a fallen Jedi turned smuggler in an effort to infiltrate the Krath, figuring the best way to stop their tour of terror is from the inside.
description.40: Trial by fire! Adam Warlock is contacted by his old ally Firelord, and warned of a new threat headed his way! His name is Zakaius, and he has judged the Infinity Watch to be guilty…and executed!
description.46: Excalibur's plane is attacked en route to Genosha, where the team has been asked to investigate mysterious violence...
description.47: When Bruce Banner's mind was able to finally control the Hulk, he never saw a reason to change back. But now the unthinkable has happened! How will Hulk's friend be able to contend with the strangest problem of all: SAVAGE BANNER?
description.48: HANDS OF THE MANDARIN PART 6 Tony Stark attends an Alcoholics Anonymous meeting on New Year's Eve.
description.50: The finale of "The River of Blood"!
description.52: Lady Sif makes the fateful decision to join Thor in Midgard.
description.53: Kaine vs. Scarlet Spider, in a heated battle in the heart of New York City! The Web of Life arc continues here!
description.55: This chromium wrap-around cover set the stage for the Age of Apocalypse in the Marvel U. Only Joe Madureira and Tim Townsend could make a depressingly dystopian future look this good!
description.56: The Fantastic Four are reunited once again!
description.57: Jean and Cable must use an amplifying machine to send a message to the X-Men in the past and warn them of coming danger.
description.61: Witness: the "Genie-ology" of Adam Destine! Pandora and Rory attend the tale of their father's super powered origin!
description.62: A Kree warrior named Shatterstar kidnaps Crystal, along with the Inhuman Devlor. It's up to the Avengers and Fantastic Force to track down Shatterstar and prove once and for all that the Kree Empire holds power no longer!
description.67: Tis the season for Force Works! In this special holiday issue, the team is planning a big X-mas bash, but they'll have to deal with a surprise gate-crasher!
description.69: It's the Secret Defenders versus….the Defenders!? That's right, the original team of Hulk, Silver Surfer, and Namor are here and they're ready to throw down!
description.71: Cable agrees to help the X-Men with their battle against Legion. Meanwhile, Locus reappears and gathers the entire X-Team to save Bobby!
description.73: The Forge Canal is uncovered, while the Strangers maintain their hold over the Doctor.
description.76: Untold secrets of the Punisher's origin! The Costas' hit team have failed to take down Castle, but that doesn't mean they've given up. Will Marvel's one-man army take out the crime family first?
description.81: In their first adventure in the'Kalarba system,'Artoo-Detoo'and'See-Threepio'arrive at'Hosk Station, where they meet the intergalactic criminal, Olag Greck!
description.82: Every'bounty hunter'on'Nar Shaddaa'is looking to bag the head of the infamous'Han Solo, but'Boba Fett'is determined to take home the trophy. And while they're busy tracking Solo, he's trying to track down'an old Jedi woman, perhaps the last hope of the'New Republic. Can Solo keep one step ahead of'the galaxy's most cutthroat gunmen and find the ancient Jedi?
description.83: In search of ancient Sith magic, the Jedi Exar Kun travels to a place of mysterious, mystical power -- a power so dark, so evil, that his very link to the light side of the Force is shattered. Jedi powers can't help him here. Only the dark side of the Force can save him -- even as it consumes him!
description.88: HANDS OF THE MANDARIN tie-in! War Machine and Century and stranded in the Chinese desert! Note: this issue contains only the Force Works story.
description.92: The Infinity Watch is ambushed by an mysterious new foe! He is known only as Strange, and he will stop at nothing until the Infinity Gems are his to control!
description.94: The Empire wishes to exploit a scientist's invention created in the name of peace. Will Luke and Han be able to ensure the device falls into Rebel hands instead?

0.text: Apocalypse is coming! It's time for the X-Men to batten down the hatches and dig their trenches because they are in for the fight of their lifetime. A fight that holds the key to the future of Mutantkind!

It's the Age of Apocalypse! Fresh from the pages of X-MEN ALPHA, Magneto
plans to put history back the way it is supposed to be, and he's sending
his X-Men out on multiple missions that will destroy the world as they
know it! See the X-Men like you've never seen them before! Quicksilver,
Rogue, Morph, Nightcrawler, Iceman, Sabretooth, Wild Child, Sunfire,
Gambit and more! Meanwhile, Apocalypse sits on his throne of human

1.text: Weapon X and Jean Grey versus Havok! Plus, witness the brutal death of a powerful warrior!

2.text: Nate's inability to follow orders is beginning to cause trouble for Bishop. Meanwhile, Apocalypse sends Domino to capture or kill a newly discovered and powerful telepath!

4.text: Infinity Watch can take down the bad guys no sweat…but how can they fight the law? It's up to Adam to convince Zakaius that they've been framed, but he'll have to do it quick, or face the wrath of Zakaius' master Domitian!

5.text: The newly Magneto-created, Colossus-led X-Men team is on a daring mission to rescue Illyana Rasputin!

6.text: Sinister plans to leave Apocalypse's side to pursue his own goals. Havok plans to take command, believing his brother Cyclops to be too weak to lead. Can Apocalypse's army hold it together or will it crumble from within?

7.text: Age of Apocalypse! See the X-Men like you've never seen them before. Magneto has assembled a roster of brave mutants to usher in an age of peaceful coexistence between humanity and mutantkind. But there are those who wish to see humanity enslaved! Enter Apocalypse!

9.text: Clea gets a much needed assist in the Dark Dimension, and “Doc” is triumphant in a battle with Strange.

11.text: In his new identity as Jack Batin, Daredevil tries to keep the streets safe.  Meanwhile, The Kingpin is plotting his revenge.

22.text: The Southern Belle fights her way through the ranks of the Assassin's Guild, and finally confronts Bella Donna herself! But what plans does the External Candra have for the two?

23.text: Has Doc Ock risen from the grave?

24.text: Your recap guide to the Spider-Man Clone Saga!

25.text: The Force Works team finds themselves traveling down under to face a mysterious monster! But they won't be alone, as they're joined by a new hero: Dreamguard!

26.text: VENOM IS REBORN! Eddie Brock reunites with his symbiote at last, but is it too late to save himself from the symbiote's wayward offspring?

27.text: A stunning betrayal leads to a devastating revelation! What does this mean for the future of the Secret Defenders?

28.text: THE FINAL SOLUTION! 3 AGAINST 1! The Guardians of the Galaxy must not only deal with Ripjak and Bubonicus, but are now dealing with the arrival of the High Evolutionary!

31.text: Makhelestan falls to currency failure and corporate clashes, spurred by Doom’s seizure of power. Fortune mourns the loss of Poet, and even Doom feels the bitter sting of his death.

32.text: Lady Deathstrike Vs. Wolverine! Season 3 starts here!

33.text: Namor plus the Ebony Blade equals trouble!

34.text: Elektra is conflicted when she is confronted with an old lover that’s a member of the cult, Snakeroot.

39.text: No more! Is Captain America finished?!

40.text: Trial by fire! Adam Warlock is contacted by his old ally Firelord, and warned of a new threat headed his way! His name is Zakaius, and he has judged the Infinity Watch to be guilty…and executed!

41.text: Alchemax deploys the powered-up Corporate Raiders to make a hostile takeover of Nightshade.

42.text: Don’t miss out! Sabretooth and Wolverine come to blows (and scratches), in a drag-out, no holds barred battle to the death. Wolvie may have gone too far, even by his own standards!

43.text: A very Generation X Christmas! When a disfigured child takes a teacher and his students hostage, it’s up to Generation X to save the class from the boy and from Orphan-Maker!

45.text: Randi, Daredevil and Wilson Fisk team up to prove Jenkins is behind the bombings.  They must work quickly because Jenkins has more bombs hidden.

54.text: Strong Guy has a serious medical emergency after taking on too much kinetic energy fighting aliens in Madripoor.

55.text: The Age of Apocalypse starts here!  Witness the birth of a whole new era for the X-Men. ALPHA kicks off Astonishing and Amazing X-Men and sets the stage for everything that is to come!
This chromium wrap-around cover set the stage for the Age of Apocalypse in the Marvel U.  Only Joe Madureira and Tim Townsend could make a depressingly dystopian future look this good!

58.text: The Age of Apocalypse begins in the present while Professor Xavier plays his part in the past.

63.text: To save the Earth in the present, Cable has sent a message to the X-Men of the past. But will it be enough? Plus, Professor X teaches his last lesson...

64.text: Gambit and Rogue face off against the deadly ninjas of the Assassin's Guild. Meanwhile, Bella Donna plots Rogue's untimely demise...

65.text: A special issue introducing you to all the characters from Cable’s timeline! What is the Askani? Who is the Askani? And what will an apocalyptic future look like for both human and mutant? A guide to a new, strange world!

66.text: It all ends here! In the final chapter of his mini-series, Vision struggles to keep the Anti-Vision at bay. Will Vision be able to save his teammates from the darkest parts of himself?

67.text: Tis the season for Force Works! In this special holiday issue, the team is planning a big X-mas bash, but they'll have to deal with a surprise gate-crasher!

68.text: A new player enters the game when the original Venom symbiote escapes its captivity! Its target? Eddie Brock!

69.text: It's the Secret Defenders versus….the Defenders!? That's right, the original team of Hulk, Silver Surfer, and Namor are here and they're ready to throw down!

70.text: CHAOS! MADNESS! The Guardians of the Galaxy are being blamed for a great deal of destruction. But is it all just another mind-trick by Ripjak?

71.text: Cable agrees to help the X-Men with their battle against Legion. Meanwhile, Locus reappears and gathers the entire X-Team to save Bobby!

73.text: The Forge Canal is uncovered, while the Strangers maintain their hold over the Doctor.

75.text: Hydra, Soviets, armored combatants. Cap and Nick Fury wage knee deep in secrets and danger.

77.text: Doctor Doom rules Latveria with an iron fist once more! However, his intentions are far from civil, when Doom uses this seat of power to inspire war and political turmoil in Makhelestan.

79.text: The murder of a US diplomat kicks off an international crisis that pulls in the likes of Nick Fury and S.H.I.E.L.D. as well as the Russian Mafioso. And caught in the middle of it all is Black Widow...but what part will she play in this conflict?

84.text: The Vision’s erratic behavior reaches new heights when he attacks fellow Avengers Giant-Man and Crystal. Will Vision achieve humanness only to see it slip away? Deathcry, Jocasta, and Ultron held captive by the avenging automaton, but for what purpose?

86.text: The birth of Genesis! Cable's son has completed his villainous transformation, and holds his father captive in the fortress of Apocalypse! It's up to Storm and Domino to break Cable out- but does he have what it takes to bring down his own son?

87.text: The battle that may claim Cap's life starts here!

88.text: HANDS OF THE MANDARIN tie-in! War Machine and Century and stranded in the Chinese desert! Note: this issue contains only the Force Works story.

89.text: Alchemax takes over Nightshade and Subject 394 is now on the loose. Can Spider-Man save the day or will he become the main target?

91.text: Penance is on the loose and there’s only one mutant who can stop her: Chamber!

92.text: The Infinity Watch is ambushed by an mysterious new foe! He is known only as Strange, and he will stop at nothing until the Infinity Gems are his to control!

93.text: HANDS OF THE MANDARIN tie-in! Force Works fights the deadly Avatars of Mandarin! Note: this issue contains only the Force Works story.

95.text: Rogue visits her first boyfriend who she put into a coma when her powers first arose. Little does she know that Bella Donna Boudreaux, ex-wife of Gambit, has dastardly plans for the two of them.

96.text: HANDS OF THE MANDARIN tie-in! Force Works may be beaten, but not beaten down! The team rallies to once again fight off Mandarin’s Avatars!

97.text: HANDS OF THE MANDARIN tie-in! War Machine and Force Works are turning the tables on Mandarin’s Avatars. Victory is in sight!

98.text: Cordelia Frost wants to join the Hellfire Club as White Queen, no matter what the cost is! And what secrets has M been hiding from the team?

99.text: Sabretooth has escaped from the X-Mansion and he's looking to rampage! The original X-Men move quickly to stop the murderous mutant before he adds to his already substantial body count.
